casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellant, v. Black, Appellee.

[Cite as State v. Black, 144 Ohio St.3d 127, 2015-Ohio-3925.]

*128(No. 2013-1947 Submitted August 11, 2015 Decided September 29, 2015.) Timothy J. McGinty, Cuyahoga County Prosecuting Attorney, and Adam M. Chaloupka, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellant. Michael B. Telep, for appellee.

{¶ 1} The judgment of the court of appeals is reversed, and the cause is remanded to that court for further proceedings on the authority of State v. Rogers, 143 Ohio St.3d 385, 2015-Ohio-2459, 38 N.E.3d 860.

O’Connor, C.J., and Pfeifer, O’Donnell, Lanzinger, Kennedy, and French, JJ., concur. O’Neill, J., dissents.
